Executive Profile
Monte E. Ford  Industry Advisor, Brightwood Capital Advisors, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships57--
Background

		Mr. Monte E. Ford serves as a Principal Partner at the Chief Information Officer Strategy Exchange. Mr. Ford is a Network Partner to Brightwood Capital Advisors, which provides growth capital to growing middle-market businesses. He serves as an Industry Advisor of Brightwood Capital Advisors, LLC. He served as an Executive Chairman of Aptean, Inc. since April 2013 and served as its President. He served as Chief Executive of Aptean Software Corporation from February 2012 ... to September 2013 and served as its Executive Chairman. He was responsible for all aspects of its business. He has served as the Chief Information Officer of AMR Corporation and Associates Frist Capital. He serves at Baylor Regional Medical Center (Grapevine). He served as the Chief Information Officer and Senior Vice President of Information Technology of American Airlines Inc. from 2001 to December 31, 2011. In that role, Mr. Ford was responsible for the American Airlines' information technology services (ITS) Group. He joined American in December 2000. He held profit and loss for the online and e-commerce functions, including the airline’s award-winning web site, AA.com for several years. He served as an Executive Vice President of Information Services at Associates First Capital Corporation since August 1999, Senior Vice President of Information Services from May 1999 to August 1999 also as Chief Information Officer. He served as the President of Associates Information Services, Inc., since April 1999; an Executive Vice President of Associates Information Services, Inc., from February 1994 to April 1999. Mr. Ford held several positions at Bank of Boston, including Senior Vice President of technology. He has nearly 20 years of executive leadership experience in the technology sector, as Chief Financial Officer of RedPrairie. He spent almost eight years with Digital Equipment Corporation. In 1983, he helped to found the Environmental Energy and Nutritional Learning Center (EENLC). He served as a Vice President of Youth Football (Southlake). He has served at Children's Medical Center of Dallas. He serves as a Director of Michaels Stores, Inc., and Sleep Development Group, LP. He has been a Director of The Michaels Companies, Inc., since September 29, 2015; Visionary Integration Professionals, LLC since April 14, 2015 and Akamai Technologies, Inc., since June 20, 2013. He served as a Director of Aptean, Inc. He serves as a Director on various community and non-profit boards. He serves on the board of Research Board and Chief Information Officer Strategy Exchange. He served as a Director of Moneygram International Inc. from August 17, 2006 to March 24, 2008 and META Group Inc. from May 2003 to October 2004. Mr. Ford served as a Director of Oncor Electric Delivery Company LLC from February 2008 to February 25, 2014 and Oncor, Inc., since February 2008. He served on several public and private boards. He since served in various capacities of service, including the Dallas Opera Board. He is recognized as one of the '50 Smartest People in Technology' by Fortune magazine for his transformative leadership and progressive thinking as the Chief Information Officer. As one of the first inductees to the CIO Hall of Fame by CIO Magazine, he is a frequent guest writer for major technology publications on topics such as the future of the technology workforce, vendor relationship management and the role of the Chief Information Officer. He is widely-regarded as a leader in the field of operations and technology. Mr. Ford holds a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration from Northeastern University.Read Full Background




