Experiential Learning | Neeley Speaker SeriesMonte E. Ford
            

            Senior Vice President and CIO
            

            American Airlines

            Monte Ford is Senior Vice President and Chief
            Information Officer at American Airlines. Widely
            regarded as a leader in the field of information
            technology, Ford joined American Airlines at a time
            when the airline needed to regain its technological
            leadership position. Ford's management has been
            critical in restoring American to the forefront of
            technological innovation.Recently named one of the "100 Most Powerful
            Executives in Corporate America" by 
            Black Enterprise

            magazine, Ford was also included as one of the "75 Most
            Powerful African-Americans in Corporate America" by the
            same publication in 2006, 2007 and 2008.  In
            recent years, he was recognized by Black Engineer as
            one of the "50 Most Important African-Americans in
            Technology." Ford has been an outspoken voice on issues of
            diversity and inclusion both in print and public
            forums, including a notable keynote address at the
            Black Data Processing Association's (BDPA) National
            Conference.  In 2009, American Airlines was named
            one of the "Best Companies for Blacks in Technology" by
            BDPA and WorkplaceDiversity.com. Ford has been recognized as one of the few members
            of CIO magazine's Hall of Fame Industry Leaders. 
            He has been a guest columnist for CIO and other
            publications - covering topics ranging from diversity
            in the technology workforce to vendor management and
            the role of CIOs reporting to CEOs.   Ford is
            a member of the Executive Leadership Council, the
            preeminent organization that recognizes the strengths,
            successes, contributions and impact of African American
            corporate business leaders.  He is also a member
            of Research Board, the CIO Strategy Exchange and Kappa
            Alpha Psi Fraternity.Prior to joining American, Ford held senior
            management positions with The Associates First Capital
            Corporation, Bank of Boston and Digital
            Equipment.  He has also served on several public
            and private boards and is currently on the board of
            Oncor Electric, the largest energy distribution utility
            in Texas.  Ford has a long history of community
            involvement in both Boston and Dallas.  He
            currently serves on the Baylor-Grapevine Board of
            Trustees and the Dallas Children's Medical Center Board
            of Trustees, and is active in community youth programs
            and church leadership groups.  Ford earned his
            B.S. in Business Administration from Northeastern
            University in Boston.  Today he and his family
            reside in Southlake, Texas.   






















